1
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
(Previously)
I realized I can't live without you.

2
00:00:15,680 --> 00:00:16,440
This is Yanin.

3
00:00:16,441 --> 00:00:18,279
The ex-girlfriend I told you about.

4
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:19,160
This is Sailom.

5
00:00:19,161 --> 00:00:20,359
My boyfriend.

6
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:21,640
And today...

7
00:00:21,720 --> 00:00:24,320
I've made a choice of my own.

8
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:27,199
But I'm here to ask for your help.

9
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,599
Can you please help your sister?

10
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:30,879
What's wrong with her?

11
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:32,719
She has Aplastic Anemia.

12
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:34,879
She needs a bone marrow transplant.

13
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:36,279
I've made my decision.

14
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,519
I'm going to help her.

15
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:39,560
I'm so proud of you, P'Doc.

16
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:47,800
"Love Like a Bike"
(Episode 8)

17
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,440
Mom.

18
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:06,200
Mom.

19
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:08,040
Nabnueng.

20
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:11,800
What is it, dear?

21
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,639
I'm thirsty.

22
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,960
Of course.

23
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:25,879
Does your back hurt?

24
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,600
Should I call the doctor?

25
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,280
It's okay, Mom.

26
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,679
It's just a bit stiff. I'll be fine soon.

27
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,920
Are you sure?

28
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,720
Take it slow.

29
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:46,160
And if it hurts,
you must tell me immediately.

30
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:47,520
Yes, Mom.

31
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,080
Thank you.

32
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:52,920
- Want some more?
- I'm fine now. Thank you.

33
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:07,240
Lada.

34
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,480
Come to visit Nabnueng?

35
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,000
Yes.

36
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,320
Nabnueng,

37
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:37,160
thank you so much for saving your sister.

38
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,880
It's nothing.

39
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,680
I'm a doctor.

40
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:44,120
Helping people is what I do.

41
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:48,120
How is Nene?

42
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:53,960
The doctor said
the transplant is finished.

43
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:57,400
She's in the sterile room now,

44
00:03:57,440 --> 00:04:00,480
waiting for the new
blood cells to start working.

45
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:03,360
Then, please tell Nene that…

46
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,840
P'Doctor Nabnueng will
come to visit her soon.

47
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,960
Of course.

48
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:10,160
Nabnueng,

49
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:14,600
you can visit Nene at home if you want.

50
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,439
P'Nabnueng!

51
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,960
How are you feeling?

52
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,600
It doesn't hurt at all.

53
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,800
Hello, Mrs. Lada.

54
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,960
Hello.

55
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,640
Hello there.

56
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,680
Why did you bring all this stuff?

57
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,080
Rations.

58
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,680
It's just a little something.

59
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:49,079
I was afraid you'd have nothing to eat,

60
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,480
so I bought out the whole shop!

61
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:54,200
Really? All of these
look like your favorites.

62
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:57,640
No, they're yours. And these are...

63
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,680
pistachio-filled!

64
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,919
Love is in the air. Look at him,

65
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:06,360
looking all handsome like a movie star.

66
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,640
You're ready to go home.

67
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,760
Am I supposed to look like a mess?

68
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,240
You should!

69
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:13,640
Oh! Are you hurt, P'Doc?!

70
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,640
It hurts like hell.

71
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,680
Such a shame. He's only 40...

72
00:05:16,720 --> 00:05:18,880
Hey, I'm not dead yet!

73
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:22,080
So, does it hurt?

74
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,920
Lada.

75
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:38,280
Don't you want to stay and
talk with your son a bit longer?

76
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:44,160
I must check on Nene. I don't want
to leave her alone for too long.

77
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:48,120
Whenever you want to see Nabnueng,

78
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,800
you're always welcome.

79
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:57,920
I'm not surprised at all that Nabnueng

80
00:05:57,960 --> 00:06:00,600
turned out to be such a good man.

81
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:03,760
I honestly don't know

82
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:09,600
if he would've been this wonderful
if I had raised him myself.

83
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,680
Phailin…

84
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,720
Thank you so much

85
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,640
for raising him so well.

86
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,320
Please keep taking care of our son.

87
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:08,280
What if...

88
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,680
the surgery didn't work?

89
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,080
What…

90
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:14,560
if the cancer cells are still there?

91
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,520
Don't think like that.

92
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,240
Good day.

93
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:37,279
Mr. Nava, are you still feeling any pain
today from where the surgery was performed?

94
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:40,200
Well... it's still a bit sore.

95
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,719
A dull, heavy kind of pain.

96
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,760
I see.

97
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:48,520
Nothing to worry about. You'll be able
to go home and recover in just a few days.

98
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:52,919
Is… there a chance
the cancer might come back?

99
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:56,880
We've successfully removed
the tumor via laparoscopy.

100
00:07:56,920 --> 00:08:01,120
Next, we'll proceed with radiation therapy
to ensure all remaining cells are gone.

101
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:03,880
You can rest easy.

102
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:06,800
If we follow the plan,
he will definitely recover.

103
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:12,880
Whether it returns depends on
his lifestyle choices from now on.

104
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,120
Thank you, Doctor.

105
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:17,680
You're very welcome.
It's my duty, after all.

106
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:19,160
Please excuse me.

107
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,640
Thank you so much.

108
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,720
See?

109
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:33,120
I told you it's treatable.

110
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:40,640
Thank you, Sky. For giving me
the courage to get treated.

111
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:43,680
Don't mention it.

112
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:46,880
We're... boyfriends now,

113
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:49,960
right?

114
00:08:51,349 --> 00:08:53,560
Want some water?

115
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,160
Oh, you're home.

116
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,800
I just finished cooking Sour Curry.

117
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,440
Go wash your hands and let's eat.

118
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,520
Grandma,

119
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,800
I have something to show you.

120
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,720
What is it?

121
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:32,920
Let me see.

122
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,400
What...

123
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,280
What kind of…

124
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,640
contract is this?

125
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,360
It's a loan agreement.

126
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:58,520
Madam Amy lent me
the money to redeem our house first.

127
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,760
She said

128
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:03,640
we can pay her back
whenever we're ready.

129
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,320
Look.

130
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:12,480
It says right here—zero interest.

131
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,280
And she even let us keep
the title deed ourselves.

132
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,720
Madam Amy is such a kind soul.

133
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,800
Yes, she is.

134
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:34,160
Now we can reopen our shop, Grandma.

135
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,920
Good morning.

136
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,800
Love Like a Bike at your service.

137
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,000
One Americano.

138
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:36,600
Hot and no sugar, as requested.

139
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,520
But I didn't order this.

140
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,760
It's a special perk for being
Dr. Nabnueng's boyfriend.

141
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,040
Thank you.

142
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,080
Let's go inside.

143
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:07,600
Don't overthink it. I'm sure
P'Doc is over his ex by now.

144
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,840
I wouldn't be so sure.

145
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:13,080
Some people still
can't let go of their exes.

146
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:14,960
Sailom?

147
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,440
Sailom.

148
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,800
Sailom.

149
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:25,960
Yes?

150
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,120
Something on your mind?

151
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,800
P'Doc…

152
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:45,080
when you called me
your boyfriend in front of your ex,

153
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:50,640
did you really mean it?
Or were you just trying to spite her?

154
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,840
I mean...

155
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:55,080
if you haven't moved on yet,

156
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,960
I understand.

157
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:02,800
Who could easily forget someone
they've been with for so long?

158
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,720
It's okay.

159
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,400
I can wait.

160
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:29,160
Sailom,

161
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,920
listen to me.

162
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,800
What I felt for Yanin

163
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,200
is over.

164
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:46,120
You probably want to know
when it ended, right?

165
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:51,320
Truth is,

166
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,800
I don't even know.

167
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,120
But what I do know

168
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,840
is that I love my new boyfriend.

169
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:07,320
The boyfriend who's sitting right here.

170
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:21,880
P'Doc!

171
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,520
Want another one?

172
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:02,560
When Sky told me he wanted
to bring his boyfriend to stay with us,

173
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:05,160
I was so curious.

174
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,720
So it was you, Nava.

175
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:10,560
Sky,

176
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:14,320
bringing your boyfriend home like this,
aren't you afraid we'll find out that

177
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:18,000
"Sky the Hunter"
has turned into a "Little Kitty?"

178
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:21,280
Tawan. You're both gonna get it.

179
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:25,520
Anyway, Mom. Like I said,

180
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:28,320
Nava needs continuous radiation therapy.

181
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:31,800
That's why I want him to
stay and recover here for a while.

182
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,720
Are you okay with that?

183
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,039
Of course, I am.

184
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:39,120
I promise, as soon as I'm better,

185
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:42,440
I'll find a job and move out.

186
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:45,960
Don't go anywhere.
Since you're Sky's boyfriend,

187
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,000
you're like a son to me now.

188
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:51,119
Just help me
keep this stubborn boy in line.

189
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,840
Aww, Mom.

190
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,120
I'm not that stubborn.

191
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,400
Don't tell Nava all that.

192
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:00,839
Alright, take a seat.
I'll come join you in a bit.

193
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:03,000
Sky will take you
inside later this evening.

194
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:05,040
- Thank you.
- Come.

195
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:14,000
Micky!

196
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,800
Who delivered the deserts?

197
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,280
Oh,

198
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,600
P'Din...

199
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,960
sent them through a courier.

200
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:38,399
So, lately, when other people touch you,

201
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:41,320
you don't feel afraid anymore, right?

202
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:42,720
Yes.

203
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:45,240
As long as I'm aware of it,

204
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:47,080
I don't feel anything.

205
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,480
But I still get a bit

206
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:54,120
startled if someone
touches me unexpectedly.

207
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:59,799
The fact that you're no
longer afraid of being touched

208
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:03,080
is a huge step forward.

209
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:05,920
I'm so proud of you, Mr. Sailom.

210
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:10,600
And I want you to be proud of yourself.

211
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:13,000
Keep believeing in the process.

212
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:16,519
If you continue with the treatment,

213
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:20,240
I'm certain you will fully recover.

214
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,520
How was your consultation?

215
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,240
Why don't you ask your friend?

216
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,400
You work in the same clinic.

217
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:44,720
I can't do that.

218
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,480
It's medical ethics.

219
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:50,440
Disclosing patient information
is strictly forbidden.

220
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:54,680
Then... can a doctor
and a patient fall in love?

221
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,440
Actually, they can't.

222
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,520
Why not?

223
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:06,160
Because therapy

224
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:09,880
requires immense trust between
the psychiatrist and the patient.

225
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:14,560
A doctor needs to see the most
vulnerable parts of a patient's heart

226
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,520
for the treatment to work.

227
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,640
If they were in love,

228
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:26,720
the patient might be afraid to
open up about their inner struggles

229
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:30,560
for fear of affecting the relationship.

230
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,560
Then, the treatment fails.

231
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,160
On the flip side,

232
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:40,960
the doctor could be seen
as using that vulnerability

233
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:44,040
to manipulate the patient's feelings.

234
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:46,720
That's why it's forbidden.

235
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,760
Then...

236
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,720
you and I... we...

237
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,600
I am a psychiatrist, that's true.

238
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:00,640
But you aren't my patient.

239
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:06,920
Wait...

240
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:10,360
so the reason you refused to
treat me from the start was...

241
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:22,720
If you were my patient,

242
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:28,320
we couldn't be boyfriends,

243
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:32,560
right?

244
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:42,440
I'm going home.

245
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,360
Sailom.

246
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,160
Need a ride?

247
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:47,880
Sailom!

248
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:58,320
Wait here for a bit.

249
00:19:58,440 --> 00:20:00,400
I'll go get you some water.

250
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,520
Thank you.

251
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:19,439
(Pedophile Doctor Arrested
for Molesting 14-Year-Old Boy.

252
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:21,600
(Shocking Discovery:
Over 20 Victims Found!)

253
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,200
Sailom.

254
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:48,560
If you can hear my voice,
I'm right here with you.

255
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:54,760
Take a deep breath in…

256
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:58,320
and slowly breathe out.

257
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:09,520
Where are you right now?

258
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:16,920
I... I'm at home.

259
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:20,360
I'm here with you, P'Doc Nabnueng.

260
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:26,960
How are you feeling?

261
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,680
He's my stepfather.

262
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:44,680
Are you alright?

263
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,280
I'm okay.

264
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,520
I really am.

265
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:55,600
Actually...

266
00:21:57,800 --> 00:22:02,520
I'm glad he's finally facing
the consequences of his actions.

267
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:08,480
He won't be able to hurt
any more unfortunate children.

268
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,560
Din,

269
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:04,400
do we still have a lot of
orders left for the bike shop?

270
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:08,520
Uh... just the Éclair fillings, and

271
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:11,200
two more trays of
Banana Cake and I'm done.

272
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:14,239
After that, mix the dough
for Taro Bua Loy for me.

273
00:23:14,240 --> 00:23:16,119
I've already steamed the taro for you.

274
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:17,360
Will do.

275
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:18,680
Oh,

276
00:23:18,720 --> 00:23:21,600
and did the duck farm
deliver more eggs?

277
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:25,280
Our Thong Yod and Foy Thong
are running low. I need to make more.

278
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:28,520
I'll check on that
once the baking's done.

279
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:36,920
And grate some coconuts for me too.

280
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,040
Got it, Grandma.

281
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:11,959
What are you here for?

282
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:13,360
Just checking on you.

283
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:20,880
Ever since you quit and started
sending desserts to the shop instead,

284
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:23,160
you haven't shown your face even once.

285
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:28,920
I was worried we'd have
nothing to sell tomorrow, so I

286
00:24:29,120 --> 00:24:30,640
came to see for myself.

287
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,760
Just say "I miss you" if you miss me.

288
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:35,920
Miss you? In your dreams.

289
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:42,000
Then go home. Your desserts will
definitely be ready by tomorrow.

290
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:47,440
Fine, I missed you.

291
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,680
Where are my snacks?

292
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:07,720
In the oven. Almost done.

293
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:28,120
Why haven't you
shown up at the cafe lately?

294
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:29,880
Avoiding me?

295
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:31,960
I'm not.

296
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:35,960
I just reopened my shop a month ago.

297
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:38,040
Things are still a bit messy.

298
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:43,680
You're really dedicated to this shop.

299
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:46,240
Of course I am.

300
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:50,200
I want this to succeed,

301
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:55,440
so my Grandma can
finally have an easy life.

302
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:59,200
Listen to you...

303
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:01,120
talking like those

304
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,800
"Young Billionaires."

305
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:09,080
Well... everyone has
to think about their future.

306
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:13,320
I'm glad to see you're
getting your life together.

307
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:17,760
You don't have to go running
around taking too many jobs.

308
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:21,160
Did you take the wrong medicine?

309
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:33,480
What about you?

310
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:39,440
How long do you plan
on being a bike mechanic?

311
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:44,440
What is that supposed to mean?

312
00:26:51,505 --> 00:26:54,525
[Some kind of bizarre throwback
to Tawan commiting manslaughter]

313
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:56,640
I think...

314
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:00,040
if you went back to being a pilot,

315
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:04,440
your future would go
much further than this.

316
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:08,680
Stay the hell out of my business.

317
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,160
Tawan.

318
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:13,560
Tawan.

319
00:27:22,520 --> 00:27:23,560
Tawan.

320
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:27,520
You're not going back because of that kid?

321
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,720
You bastard!

322
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:32,560
I told you to stay out of it!

323
00:27:34,840 --> 00:27:36,200
So, it's true.

324
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:37,960
Goddamnit.

325
00:27:44,280 --> 00:27:47,440
If punching me makes
you feel better, go ahead.

326
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:58,840
It was an accident.

327
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:00,840
Nobody wanted it to happen.

328
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,840
But I messed up!

329
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:07,560
Som died because of me!

330
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:09,680
How much longer are you
going to blame yourself!?

331
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:14,920
Have you ever thought about
how the people who love you feel?!

332
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:21,720
Listen to me.

333
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:26,040
You can feel guilty for the
rest of your life if you want,

334
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:29,120
because forgiving yourself

335
00:28:30,160 --> 00:28:32,040
is never easy.

336
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:35,080
But don't just do it for yourself.

337
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:38,000
Do it for Auntie Phailin,

338
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:40,360
your family,

339
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:44,040
the ones you love,

340
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,560
and the people who love you.

341
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:54,160
Stop torturing yourself.

342
00:29:05,760 --> 00:29:07,080
Need a hug?

343
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:09,680
My chest is free.

344
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:45,640
I don't want to go back to the States.

345
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:50,240
Can I just stay here
with you like this forever?

346
00:29:53,280 --> 00:29:55,320
You can't do that.

347
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:58,640
You have to go back
and finish your studies, okay?

348
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,320
It's so unfair.

349
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:08,760
We've only just gotten close,

350
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:10,920
and now I have to leave?

351
00:30:12,960 --> 00:30:16,320
I haven't had enough of
these moments with you yet.

352
00:30:18,920 --> 00:30:20,640
What kind of moments?

353
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,680
Moments like this.

354
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:07,320
One, two, go.

355
00:32:09,560 --> 00:32:10,880
P'Dindin!

356
00:32:11,080 --> 00:32:13,280
Hello, Auntie Pailin.

357
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:14,960
Hey there, Looksoh.

358
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:19,880
What brings you here today? You usually
don't deliver the desserts yourself.

359
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:23,040
I just… missed everyone at the café.

360
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:26,400
Always the smooth talker, aren't you?

361
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:30,079
Alright, I'll go transfer
the payment for the desserts.

362
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,440
Thank you.

363
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:36,960
Looking for someone?

364
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:38,600
Oh…

365
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:40,600
just looking around.

366
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,920
Haven't seen you in days.

367
00:32:54,280 --> 00:32:56,920
I was about
to file a missing person's report.

368
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,000
Oh…

369
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:00,360
Sky.

370
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:03,360
Hey. Thought I was Tawan?

371
00:33:04,600 --> 00:33:07,080
So... where is he?

372
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:09,200
Oh, Tawan told me

373
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:11,240
he's done with fixing bikes.

374
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:14,760
Said he's going to work in Bangkok,

375
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:18,840
so I'm taking over for him.

376
00:33:19,840 --> 00:33:21,120
Bangkok?

377
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:23,240
Didn't he talk to you about it?

378
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:26,600
No, he didn't.

379
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:31,280
And... uh...

380
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,360
Hello.

381
00:33:34,160 --> 00:33:38,400
Oh, of course. You can come
to take your bicycle this evening.

382
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:11,960
Thank you so much for throwing
this farewell party for me.

383
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:16,120
The food is amazing, and the
dipping sauce is so spicy.

384
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:23,000
I'm going to miss your cooking
so much when I'm over there.

385
00:34:23,200 --> 00:34:24,960
Only missing the food?

386
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:27,280
What about the "person?"

387
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:29,000
He's spicy too.

388
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,200
Looksoh.

389
00:34:32,720 --> 00:34:33,919
Sailom,

390
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,639
Hurry up and graduate.

391
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:37,760
Have some pity on this guy over here.

392
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:43,320
Don't make him wait too long,
or he might just die from heartbreak.

393
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:56,200
P'Doc…

394
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:59,000
don't worry about me.

395
00:34:59,520 --> 00:35:02,400
I'll study hard,
graduate as fast as I can,

396
00:35:02,560 --> 00:35:05,120
and come straight back to you.

397
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,640
I know.

398
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:16,440
Can I have one more
piece of grilled squid?

399
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:21,360
You won't get to eat this
over there. Take ten pieces.

400
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:45,880
I'm really gonna miss you so much.

401
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:50,280
Don't be so dramatic.
He's going to study, not to war.

402
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:52,040
Right, Sailom?

403
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:54,680
Sailom?

404
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:58,800
What's wrong?

405
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:02,720
I'm scared.

406
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:06,640
What are you afraid of?

407
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:09,600
Worried P'Doc will leave you?

408
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:13,239
If it's about that,

409
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:15,400
you have nothing to fear.

410
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:18,840
Besides, we can stay
connected all the time now.

411
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:22,960
You can call him
whenever you miss him, right?

412
00:36:24,560 --> 00:36:26,120
I wouldn't be so sure.

413
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:29,240
Even couples who've been
together for ages break up.

414
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:31,096
They broke up before
he started dating our friend.

415
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:34,360
No, what I'm saying is they
broke up because of the distance.

416
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:46,240
But maybe you two will make it.

417
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:48,080
Don't overthink it.

418
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,880
Sailom. Where are you going?

419
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:55,040
Sailom!

420
00:36:58,080 --> 00:36:59,336
I was trying to look out for him.

421
00:36:59,360 --> 00:37:00,880
Look out for him, my ass.

422
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:02,800
What if he ends up getting hurt later?

423
00:37:24,160 --> 00:37:25,480
P'Doc.

424
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:27,680
Sailom?

425
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:29,960
Is something wrong?

426
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:40,880
You're really going
to wait for me, right?

427
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:43,520
Of course, I'll wait.

428
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:47,160
We won't end up...

429
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,680
breaking up like you
and your ex, will we?

430
00:38:01,680 --> 00:38:02,800
Sailom,

431
00:38:03,960 --> 00:38:05,720
Yanin and I broke up,

432
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:09,800
because she left me
waiting without any goal.

433
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,160
But with you,

434
00:38:12,720 --> 00:38:15,680
I'm certain it won't be like that.

435
00:38:17,720 --> 00:38:20,200
Seeing you rush here today

436
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:25,080
only makes me confident

437
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:30,120
that waiting for you is worth it.

438
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,920
You said it.

439
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:38,920
Now you have to promise me.

440
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:44,040
While I'm gone, you aren't
allowed to look at anyone else.

441
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:48,240
Promise me.

442
00:38:49,680 --> 00:38:51,160
I promise.

443
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:55,680
And you have to video call me every day.

444
00:38:57,440 --> 00:39:01,720
If you don't, I'll fly back here
and deal with you myself!

445
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:07,800
I will.

446
00:39:10,760 --> 00:39:12,400
Now, come here.

447
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:34,640
I miss you so much.

448
00:39:35,040 --> 00:39:36,920
I miss you too.

449
00:39:39,280 --> 00:39:41,160
I really want to see you.

450
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:43,400
I love you, Sailom.

451
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:47,680
And how's uni going?

452
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,920
I'm so exhausted.

453
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:53,040
I just want to whine to you so much.

454
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:55,040
Go ahead.

455
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:57,480
I'm so exhausted.

456
00:39:57,520 --> 00:40:00,120
I've been studying day and night.

457
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:04,680
And I was late for class today because
I stayed up late reading last night.

458
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:11,040
Sailom,

459
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:13,960
the café is organizing
a cycling trip next month.

460
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:18,203
It's such a shame
you won't be here to join us.

461
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:23,720
Sailom?

462
00:40:25,240 --> 00:40:26,640
Sailom!

463
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,080
Goodnight.

464
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:04,440
(Sailom)

465
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:51,040
(P'Doc)

466
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:24,800
(P'Doc)

467
00:42:48,680 --> 00:42:50,280
I want this one.

468
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:52,240
- One of each, right?
- Yes, ma'am.

469
00:42:52,280 --> 00:42:54,376
Go wait at the table, dear.
I'll bring them over in a bit.

470
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:55,800
Okay!

471
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:00,120
Nabnueng!

472
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:04,120
- Yes, Mom?
- The clinic's order is almost ready.

473
00:43:04,320 --> 00:43:05,840
Got it, Mom.

474
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:15,480
Mom,

475
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,199
he's been staring at his phone

476
00:43:18,200 --> 00:43:20,400
and moping like this for a week now.

477
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:23,400
It's exactly how he was
when he broke up with P'Yanin.

478
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:24,920
I don't think so, sweetie.

479
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:30,960
Nabnueng, your coffee is ready.

480
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:55,400
Here, I'll help you.

481
00:43:55,440 --> 00:43:56,640
Thanks.

482
00:44:14,200 --> 00:44:15,480
P'Dindin.

483
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:17,720
Hey, Looksoh.

484
00:44:18,960 --> 00:44:21,600
I've only been gone for a few weeks.

485
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:23,440
How did it get so crowded here?

486
00:44:23,480 --> 00:44:26,439
It's because P'Nava
started a TikTok channel

487
00:44:26,440 --> 00:44:29,520
and he's been putting out
P'Mickey and P'Zoom content.

488
00:44:31,080 --> 00:44:32,840
Wow, that's cool.

489
00:44:32,880 --> 00:44:37,680
But with so many customers,
can Sky handle it all by himself?

490
00:44:37,720 --> 00:44:40,760
Oh, P'Sky doesn't do
the repairs anymore.

491
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:46,160
He hired mechanics
and became a part dealer instead.

492
00:44:47,880 --> 00:44:53,880
He says selling parts
is more profitable than fixing them.

493
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:57,280
When he's not meeting clients,

494
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:59,960
he maybe helps P'Nava with wedding shoots.

495
00:45:00,080 --> 00:45:03,120
And... what about Tawan?

496
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:04,640
What's he doing now?

497
00:45:04,680 --> 00:45:06,280
P'Tawan's...

498
00:45:06,320 --> 00:45:07,600
Dindin.

499
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:39,960
Now, give each other a little kiss.

500
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:42,800
Okay.

501
00:45:42,840 --> 00:45:44,040
Is the light okay?

502
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:47,720
Beautiful.

503
00:45:48,280 --> 00:45:50,320
Getting tired?

504
00:45:50,480 --> 00:45:51,879
Not at all, babe.

505
00:45:51,880 --> 00:45:52,960
Give me a kiss?

506
00:45:54,840 --> 00:45:56,960
I hired you guys to work!

507
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:59,440
How can you be
sweeter than the grooms?!

508
00:45:59,480 --> 00:46:01,720
Get back to shooting!

509
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:06,360
Still at it?!

510
00:46:06,400 --> 00:46:07,840
Alright, alright.

511
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:11,760
- How's the reflect?
- Good enough.

512
00:46:12,600 --> 00:46:14,440
How much further
are you going to walk?!

513
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:15,960
Dindin!

514
00:46:22,040 --> 00:46:23,640
Where the hell have you been?

515
00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:26,440
I called, I texted, and you never replied.

516
00:46:26,880 --> 00:46:28,239
What is wrong with you?

517
00:46:28,240 --> 00:46:30,560
I went back to being a pilot,
just like you wanted.

518
00:46:30,600 --> 00:46:33,760
Were you flying in outer space?
Why didn't you reply?

519
00:46:34,320 --> 00:46:35,760
I'm sorry.

520
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:39,080
I just wanted you to be proud of me,

521
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:42,080
as much as I'm proud of you.

522
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:46,200
I've worked so hard to be a pilot again

523
00:46:47,440 --> 00:46:49,280
just to ask you to be my boyfriend.

524
00:46:50,200 --> 00:46:51,400
Wait…

525
00:46:53,800 --> 00:46:55,560
what did you just say?

526
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:56,920
Are you deaf?

527
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:01,200
What's it gonna be?

528
00:47:01,560 --> 00:47:03,120
Will you be my boyfriend?

529
00:47:06,720 --> 00:47:07,920
Fine.

530
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:09,640
I guess I will.

531
00:47:13,280 --> 00:47:15,480
You look pretty hot in that uniform.

532
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:23,560
Let's find somewhere… to take it off.

533
00:47:26,280 --> 00:47:28,520
I've been wanting to
undress a pilot for a long time.

534
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:30,719
Just say you're horny.

535
00:47:30,720 --> 00:47:32,240
And you're not?

536
00:47:48,920 --> 00:47:50,200
P'Doc,

537
00:47:50,400 --> 00:47:52,000
come swim with me!

538
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,440
Don't let me be alone!

539
00:47:55,160 --> 00:47:56,560
P'Doc!

540
00:47:59,680 --> 00:48:02,320
You told me to wait...

541
00:48:05,680 --> 00:48:07,760
and I'm still here, waiting for you.

542
00:48:49,320 --> 00:48:50,840
P'Doc Nabnueng!

543
00:49:00,680 --> 00:49:03,680
I knew I'd find you here!

544
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:32,000
Why didn't you answer my calls?

545
00:49:33,080 --> 00:49:35,120
You didn't answer mine either.

546
00:49:39,080 --> 00:49:42,800
It's because of the time zones,
so our schedules never matched.

547
00:49:44,680 --> 00:49:46,120
Wait a minute.

548
00:49:46,760 --> 00:49:48,880
Are you doing this…

549
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:51,560
to get back at me?

550
00:49:55,880 --> 00:49:58,200
It was supposed to be a surprise.

551
00:50:01,400 --> 00:50:05,240
I've decided to drop out from the U.S.
university

552
00:50:06,360 --> 00:50:08,639
and transfer back to
a Thai one.

553
00:50:08,640 --> 00:50:11,080
Our time will finally be in sync.

554
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:13,200
Now,

555
00:50:14,080 --> 00:50:17,280
you have to answer my video calls.

556
00:50:17,560 --> 00:50:19,480
No more excuses.

557
00:50:21,760 --> 00:50:23,200
I will.

558
00:50:24,520 --> 00:50:27,280
I'll video call you...

559
00:50:28,480 --> 00:50:30,200
until we're old.

560
00:50:30,560 --> 00:50:31,600
How's that?

561
00:50:33,280 --> 00:50:35,200
Is this a proposal?

562
00:50:36,320 --> 00:50:37,640
Do you want to?

563
00:50:38,360 --> 00:50:39,360
Come.

564
00:50:39,361 --> 00:50:42,280
Let's go register our marriage right now.

565
00:50:43,240 --> 00:50:45,480
Whoa... calm down, P'Doc.

566
00:50:45,920 --> 00:50:47,880
I'm still a student.

567
00:50:51,320 --> 00:50:52,880
I missed you so much.

568
00:51:46,080 --> 00:51:47,400
P'Doc.

569
00:51:48,600 --> 00:51:49,880
Yes?

570
00:51:50,720 --> 00:51:55,000
Do you remember the first time
you invited me to go cycling?

571
00:51:57,960 --> 00:51:59,880
Of course I do. Why?

572
00:52:01,800 --> 00:52:05,560
Actually, I didn't like cycling back then.

573
00:52:06,600 --> 00:52:08,480
I only went

574
00:52:09,520 --> 00:52:11,120
because of you.

575
00:52:12,760 --> 00:52:14,119
I already knew that.

576
00:52:14,120 --> 00:52:15,240
Huh?

577
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:20,120
Your eyes gave it away.

578
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:22,400
Admit it.

579
00:52:29,040 --> 00:52:30,360
What about now?

580
00:52:31,120 --> 00:52:33,400
Do you like cycling more?

581
00:52:39,880 --> 00:52:41,600
I love it more than anything.

582
00:52:48,920 --> 00:52:50,480
But honestly,

583
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:53,720
I'd do anything

584
00:52:54,680 --> 00:52:56,640
as long as I'm with you.

585
00:52:57,760 --> 00:53:01,200
That's all I ever need.

